org.javaavc.ffmpeg

Class NativeUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.javaavc.ffmpeg.NativeUtils

  • public class NativeUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains methods that help works with native code.

    This class support only Linux and Windows operation systems and 32 and 64 bit architectures.

    Version:
    3.1.1
    Author:
    Dmitriy Zavodnikov (d.zavodnikov@gmail.com)

      • getJarFileByResName

        public static java.io.File getJarFileByResName(java.lang.String resName)
                                        throws java.io.IOException
        This method found JAR-file with defined resources name.

        Remember that:

        1. If the name begins with a '/', then the absolute name of the resource is the portion of the name following the '/'.
        2. Otherwise, the absolute name is of the following form: "package_name/name".

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • unpackNative

        public static java.io.File unpackNative(java.lang.String libName)
                                 throws java.io.IOException
        Unpack native library from JAR-file to temporary directory and return File to it.

        Will be found resource in format LibName_OsName_Arch (for example, mylib_linux_64), copied into temporary directory and returned File of this copy (for example, /tmp/mylib_linux_64).

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • runProcess

        public static java.lang.Process runProcess(java.io.File bin,
                           java.lang.String command)
        Run executable file in separate process. Supported Linux and Windows.

        For Linux -- see shared library search paths:

        1. Shared Libraries -- tldp.org.

        For windows -- DLLs search paths:

        1. The current directory.
        2. %WINDOWS%\System32.
        3. %WINDOWS%.
        4. The directories listed in the PATH environment variable.
        Note: The LIBPATH environment variable is not used.
